I"(<p>Assuming you are inside the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">adb shell</code>, running the below commands would remove
all the unnecessary apps from Redmi Note 10. This does NOT require you to be root.
However, as expected, the .apk of these apps would still be available inside
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/data/app</code> folder.</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>pm uninstall <span class="nt">--user</span> 0 com.miui.screenrecorder                     <span class="c"># Screen recorder</span>
